# Pentagon plane mesh - 4x4 grid of pentagon faces (16 faces), Y-up
# 25 corner vertices + 8 midpoint vertices = 33 vertices total
# N=4, cellSize=0.75, world size 3x3, range [-1.5, 1.5] in XZ
# Each adjacent column pair (0,1) and (2,3) produces 2 pentagons.
# The shared midpoint vertex is shifted to the left-cell center x,
# creating visually distinct (non-rectangular) pentagonal faces.
# Winding: CCW for +Y normal.

# --- Corner vertices (5x5 grid) ---
v -1.5  0.0 -1.5
v -0.75 0.0 -1.5
v  0.0  0.0 -1.5
v  0.75 0.0 -1.5
v  1.5  0.0 -1.5

v -1.5  0.0 -0.75
v -0.75 0.0 -0.75
v  0.0  0.0 -0.75
v  0.75 0.0 -0.75
v  1.5  0.0 -0.75

v -1.5  0.0  0.0
v -0.75 0.0  0.0
v  0.0  0.0  0.0
v  0.75 0.0  0.0
v  1.5  0.0  0.0

v -1.5  0.0  0.75
v -0.75 0.0  0.75
v  0.0  0.0  0.75
v  0.75 0.0  0.75
v  1.5  0.0  0.75

v -1.5  0.0  1.5
v -0.75 0.0  1.5
v  0.0  0.0  1.5
v  0.75 0.0  1.5
v  1.5  0.0  1.5

# --- Midpoint vertices shifted to left-cell center x ---
# Pair 0: col_right=1, left-cell center x = (0+1)/2*0.75 - 1.5 = -1.125
v -1.125 0.0 -1.125
v -1.125 0.0 -0.375
v -1.125 0.0  0.375
v -1.125 0.0  1.125

# Pair 1: col_right=3, left-cell center x = (2+3)/2*0.75 - 1.5 = 0.375
v  0.375 0.0 -1.125
v  0.375 0.0 -0.375
v  0.375 0.0  0.375
v  0.375 0.0  1.125

# --- Pentagon faces: winding BL->BR->M->TR->TL for pent1, BL->BR->TR->TL->M for pent2 ---
# Pair 0 (columns 0,1):
f  6  7 26  2  1
f  7  8  3  2 26
f 11 12 27  7  6
f 12 13  8  7 27
f 16 17 28 12 11
f 17 18 13 12 28
f 21 22 29 17 16
f 22 23 18 17 29

# Pair 1 (columns 2,3):
f  8  9 30  4  3
f  9 10  5  4 30
f 13 14 31  9  8
f 14 15 10  9 31
f 18 19 32 14 13
f 19 20 15 14 32
f 23 24 33 19 18
f 24 25 20 19 33
